{
  "text": "To generate an overview of microbial community composition during the bloom (Figs 2 and 3) , the 16S and 18S rRNA amplicon libraries (raw reads) were primer-trimmed using Cutadapt (v 1.18) [CITATION_1] and analyzed using QIIME2 (v 2018.6) [CITATION_2] . The DADA2 23 plugin in QIIME2 was used to generate exact sequence variants (ESVs), which were classified using the QIIME2 naive Bayes classifier trained on 99% Operational Taxonomic Units (OTUs) from the SILVA rRNA database (v 132) [CITATION_3] after trimming to the primer region. Taxonomic bar plots were generated using QIIME2.",
